<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-01-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="697" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d697">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Message of the President.</hi></head>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">To the Senate of the United
                                States:</hi></p>
                        <p>I transmit herewith in response to the Senate resolution of December 21,
                            1896, addressed to the Secretary of State, a report of that officer,
                            covering a list of persons claiming to be citizens of the United States,
                            who have been arrested on the Island of Cuba since February 24, 1895, to
                            the present time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grover Cleveland.</hi></signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <dateline rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive
                                        Mansion</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-01-25"><hi rend="italic">January 25,
                                    1897.</hi></date></dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>